<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb7835fa3-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea" identifier="/us/usc/t5/s105"><num value="105">§ 105.</num><heading> Executive agency</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">For the purpose of this title, “Executive agency” means an Executive department, a Government corporation, and an independent establishment.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idb7835fa4-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea">(<ref href="/us/pl/89/554">Pub. L. 89–554</ref>, <date date="1966-09-06">Sept. 6, 1966</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/80/379">80 Stat. 379</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idb7835fa5-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="historicalAndRevision" id="idb7835fa6-5e84-11f1-a692-ec26948f6fea"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Historical and Revision Notes</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">The section is supplied to avoid the necessity for defining “Executive agency” each time it is used in this title.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
